  "signature": "ed25519:b2c3d4e5f6a7b8c9d0e1f2a3b4c5d6e7f8a9b0c1d2e3f4a5b6c7d8e9f0a1b2c3",
  "hasWeakener": [],
  "hasCredibilityFactor": [
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Software quality assurance",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA solver must be under documented version control with traceable regression test results; all analysis scripts archived in institutional repository with change log.",
      "rationale": "Ansys Mechanical 2022 R2 used under institutional license with version-controlled input decks stored in Git repository. Regression test suite (ANSYS Verification Manual cases VM1–VM12 relevant to structural statics) executed and archived. DePuy Synthes and FDA independently ran equivalent solvers under their own QMS procedures. Software qualification records available for audit. Achieved Gradation 3 (independent multi-site QA) exceeds required Gradation 2."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Code verification must demonstrate correct implementation of governing equations through at least one benchmark problem with known analytical solution relevant to structural mechanics.",
      "rationale": "Euler-Bernoulli beam bending benchmark and Hertzian contact patch benchmark executed in Ansys; results match analytical solutions to within 0.3% and 1.1% respectively. Code verification documentation submitted as supplementary material to FDA submission package. Achieved level meets required level."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Mesh convergence study must demonstrate QoI change of less than 5% between successive refinement levels; Richardson extrapolation or GCI reported.",
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study performed on representative screw-rod construct: coarse (element edge ~0.8 mm), medium (0.4 mm), fine (0.2 mm). GCI for stiffness QoI: 1.8%. QoI variation between medium and fine mesh: 1.1%, well below 5% threshold. Final production mesh uses medium density for computational efficiency. Achieved Gradation 3 exceeds required Gradation 2."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver convergence tolerances must be documented and force/displacement residuals reported for each simulation run.",
      "rationale": "Newton-Raphson iteration used for nonlinear contact; force residual tolerance set to 0.1% of applied load. All 11 simulation runs converged within 50 substeps; no unconverged increments recorded. Solver log files archived. Achieved Gradation 2 exceeds required Gradation 1."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "A documented peer-review process or independent model recreation must be completed prior to result submission; checklist of analyst assumptions must be reviewed by a second qualified engineer.",
      "rationale": "FDA analyst independently recreated boundary conditions and loading from ASTM F1717 protocol description and cross-checked against DePuy Synthes model setup. Discrepancies in friction coefficient assignment (0.2 vs 0.25 at rod-screw interface) identified and resolved by consensus; sensitivity analysis showed less than 2% QoI impact. Analyst assumption checklist reviewed and signed off by second engineer. Achieved level meets required level."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "rationale": "Continuum elastoplastic model (bilinear isotropic hardening, Ti-6Al-4V: E=114 GPa, σ_y=880 MPa, E_t=1.1 GPa) selected based on published literature and coupon-level material validation. Frictional contact (Coulomb, μ=0.22) at rod-screw and screw-block interfaces. Large-deformation formulation (NLGEOM ON) activated to capture post-yield response relevant to 40 mm displacement QoI. Model form uncertainty quantified via ensemble spread across three independent implementations; inter-model QoI standard deviation 3.2% of mean. Required Gradation 3 reflects moderate model risk; achieved level meets required level. Note: acceptanceCriteria rationale embedded here per team convention — the structured field is intentionally managed at the program level rather than duplicated per factor."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties must be sourced from traceable coupon tests or peer-reviewed literature; geometric inputs must be derived from calibrated CMM measurements with reported uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "Ti-6Al-4V material properties from ASTM E8 tensile coupon tests on production bar stock (n=5; CV<2%). Implant geometry from CMM measurement of production screws; dimensional tolerance ±0.01 mm. UHMWPE block modulus from supplier certificate of conformance, validated against published values. All input uncertainties propagated via Monte Carlo (N=1000 samples); 95th-percentile input uncertainty contribution to stiffness QoI: 2.8%. Achieved Gradation 3 exceeds required Gradation 2."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test specimens must be production-representative implants from documented lot with traceability to manufacturing records; minimum sample size must be justified by statistical power analysis.",
      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs from production lot PL-2019-447; manufacturing records on file. Sample size justified by power analysis targeting 80% power to detect 10% QoI difference at α=0.05 (n_min=9). Constructs assembled per ASTM F1717 by trained technicians at two independent laboratories (Lab A: n=6, Lab B: n=5). Inter-laboratory variability assessed; pooled CV for stiffness 4.1%. Achieved level meets required level."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation testing must cover at least two clinically relevant loading configurations or boundary condition variants to bound the model prediction space; single-condition testing requires documented justification.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed under a single ASTM F1717 compression-bending configuration (35 mm offset, quasi-static 1 mm/min crosshead speed). A second configuration varying offset distance (25 mm) was planned but not executed due to resource constraints. This factor therefore achieves Gradation 2 against a required Gradation 3; the gap is acknowledged and mitigated by the conservative nature of the 35 mm offset (worst-case clinically). The structured acceptanceCriteria field above documents the requirement; the gap is flagged as a known shortfall in the overall credibility summary."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model boundary conditions and loading must be shown to match experimental setup parameters within documented tolerance; any deviations must be assessed for QoI impact.",
      "rationale": "Applied displacement boundary conditions mapped directly from crosshead displacement transducer records; load cell data used to verify applied force. Fixture compliance measured and incorporated into model as spring boundary condition (k_fixture = 18,400 N/mm). Offset distance verified by CMM of assembled fixture: 35.02 ± 0.08 mm vs nominal 35 mm. All deviations quantified; maximum QoI impact of fixture compliance correction: 1.7% on stiffness. Achieved Gradation 3 exceeds required Gradation 2."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric must be pre-specified; E/uval ratio must be computed and reported against a pre-defined threshold; comparison must account for both model and experimental uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "Three QoIs compared: construct stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement. Validation metric: E/uval ratio (ASME V&V 10.1) with uval computed from combined model uncertainty (Monte Carlo) and experimental uncertainty (inter-specimen CV, measurement uncertainty). Pre-specified acceptance threshold: E/uval < 1.96 (95% confidence). Results: stiffness E/uval=1.31, yield force E/uval=0.94, force@40mm E/uval=1.61; all pass. Achieved Gradation 3 meets required Gradation 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "rationale": "Stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are the three QoIs specified in ASTM F1717 and directly correspond to the clinical performance attributes (construct rigidity, fatigue life proxy, and post-yield load-carrying capacity) identified in the risk analysis. QoI selection reviewed and approved by clinical affairs team. The required level of 2 reflects that QoIs are standard and well-established for this device type; achieved level of 3 reflects additional traceability to clinical risk documentation. Program-level acceptance criteria for this factor are maintained in the master credibility plan document rather than repeated here."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities must use the same implant geometry, material lot, and loading protocol as the COU; any differences between validation scenario and intended COU must be bounded by sensitivity analysis.",
      "rationale": "Validation constructs are identical in geometry and material to the COU device (production 7.5 mm non-cannulated pedicle screw). Loading protocol is ASTM F1717 as specified in COU. The COU represents a single-level lumbar fusion scenario; the F1717 fixture is a conservative surrogate (no load sharing from bone). Sensitivity analysis confirms that adding bone-equivalent load sharing reduces construct loads, making the validation scenario conservative relative to the COU. Achieved Gradation 3 meets required Gradation 3."
    }
  ],
  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/decision/cou1-accepted-20260419",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/org/fda-cdrh-osel",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed their required gradation levels. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved Gradation 2 vs required Gradation 3) is mitigated by the conservative nature of the tested configuration and is documented in the credibility summary. All three QoIs pass the pre-specified E/uval < 1.96 acceptance threshold. The overall credibility of the FEA model ensemble is judged sufficient to support the Medium assurance level decision for the non-cannulated pedicle screw compression-bending COU.",
